      "writtenOn": "2026-03-19T18:22:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It seems fairly clear to me that it\u0027s unambiguous because a string literal is an unambiguous token: it fits right in with the existing PrimateExpr grammar:\n\n```\nPrimaryExpr \u003d\n\tOperand |\n\tPrimaryExpr Selector |\n\tPrimaryExpr Index |\n\tPrimaryExpr Arguments |\n\tPrimaryExpr string_lit .\n```\n\nAdded EBNF to the proposal.",
