      "writtenOn": "2026-03-08T09:58:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note that this is different from the interpolations signature, which is a single list with alternating string and value. But that is probably fine.\n\nEither way, any reason to deviate from this form? Did you evaluate which results in nicer code?\n\nIt would be good to have at least one realistic Go implementation of such a function in this proposal. (or reference to a different CL with one or two)",
      "revId": "9c92333dfad055d156b42db1e14200135df4eb86",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
