      "writtenOn": "2026-03-08T09:58:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That in itself is not sufficient proof it is not ambiguous or can lead to problems down the line. Also we want to avoid lookahead.\n\nAlso, it should be considered what this disallows in the future. For instance, we would not be able to allow lists without commas anymore [1 2 3]. \n\ntry: func\na: try \"foo\" {}\nb: try \"foo\"   // we might want to allow this try form in the future.",
      "revId": "9c92333dfad055d156b42db1e14200135df4eb86",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "59180e56_4554c370",
        "filename": "designs/language/4295-tagged-string-literals.md",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 255,
      "author": {
        "id": 1007275
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-19T18:22:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "```\nb: try \"foo\" // we might want to allow this try form in the future.\n```\n\nAFAICS this is already ambiguous with respect to the function call syntax.\nFor example:\n\n```\ntry: func\nb: try ((a.b? + 1) * 3)\n```\n\nIs that an invocation of the `try` function or an actual `try` statement.\nI don\u0027t think this proposal makes that any harder or easier.",
      "parentUuid": "7dc61b94_310b06fb",
      "revId": "9c92333dfad055d156b42db1e14200135df4eb86",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "86abe8e1_af16d9c5",
        "filename": "designs/language/4295-tagged-string-literals.md",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 255,
      "author": {
        "id": 1007275
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-20T12:04:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I just realised that we already have a similar ambiguity with respect to `if`:\n\n```\nimport \"strconv\"\n\n_a: {\n\tif: strconv.Atoi\n\tif(\"2\") \u003d\u003d 2 {\n\t\ta: 2\n\t}\n\ta: *1 | _\n}\na: _a.a\n```\nThis exports as `{\"a\": 1}`, when arguably it could be a syntax error.",
      "parentUuid": "59180e56_4554c370",
      "revId": "9c92333dfad055d156b42db1e14200135df4eb86",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
